fields.title: HTML_intro1
fields.code:
Hello Cub! Welcome to the world of HTML:

Your Journey Begins Here!

Get ready to embark on an exciting adventure into the realm of web development with us. Let's dive into the vibrant universe of HTML[HyperText Markup Language] - the foundational building block of all things web!

What is HTML?

HTML is like the skeleton of a webpage. It gives structure to your content, allowing browsers to understand how to display text, images, links, and more.

The Structure of HTML

Every HTML document is build upon a simple structure. Here's what the structure of an HTML page looks like:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>My HTML Page</title>
</head>
<body>
</body>
</html>

Breaking it Down:

<html>, <head>,<body>, and so on are all called Tags. Tags carry specific information within them, they are declared by <tag> [openning tag] and</tag>[closing tag]. They act like containers and all tell the browser about the kind of information that lies within them.For example, <p> This is a paragraph </p> tells the browser that what is within the <p> tag is a paragraph.

<!DOCTYPE html>: This declaration tells the browser to expect an HTML5 document.

<html>: The root element that wraps all your content.

<head>: Contains meta-information about your document [like title, character set, and linked styles].

<body>: This is where you place all your visible content.

Why Learn HTML?

Empower your creativity: Build stunning websites from scratch!

Foundation for your languages: HTML is the first step towards mastering CSS, javaScript, and more!

In-Demand Skill: Web development skills are highly valued in today's job market.

In this bootcamp, we're going to provide you everything you need to get heads-on with html including an interactive code editor.

The Web: A Double-Edged Sword

The internet, built by diligent web developers, has revolutionized communication and commerce. They craft intricate systems, turning lines of code into interactive experiences. These digital architects design websites and applications that power our modern world.


The Shadowy Side: Hackers

However, this vibrant ecosystem is constantly threatened by hackers. These individuals seek to exploit vulnerabilities in systems, often with malicious intent. Their actions range from data breaches and identity theft to the disruption of critical infrastructure.

class Dog:
    # Constructor method to initialize attributes
    def __init__(self, name, breed):
        self.name = name  # Attribute for dog's name
        self.breed = breed  # Attribute for dog's breed

    # Method to make the dog bark
    def bark(self):
        return f"{self.name} says Woof!"


# Creating instances of the Dog class
dog1 = Dog("Buddy", "Golden Retriever")
dog2 = Dog("Max", "Beagle")

# Accessing attributes
print(dog1.name)  # Output: Buddy
print(dog2.breed)  # Output: Beagle

# Calling methods
print(dog1.bark())  # Output: Buddy says Woof!
print(dog2.bark())  # Output: Max says Woof!

fields.title: python16.4
fields.code:
class Animal:
    def __init__(self, name):  # Fixed the constructor method name to __init__
        self.name = name

    def speak(self):
        return "Some sound"

class Dog(Animal):  # Dog inherits from Animal
    def speak(self):
        return f"{self.name} says Woof!"

class Cat(Animal):  # Cat inherits from Animal
    def speak(self):
        return f"{self.name} says Meow!"

# Creating instances
dog = Dog("Buddy")
cat = Cat("Whiskers")

# Calling the speak method for both instances
print(dog.speak())  # Output: Buddy says Woof!
print(cat.speak())  # Output: Whiskers says Meow!

fields.text: What does HTML stand for?
fields.explanation: HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language, which is the standard language used to create web pages.

fields.text: Which of the following is the correct way to create a paragraph in HTML?
fields.explanation:
The correct tag for creating a paragraph in HTML is

, which stands for paragraph.

fields.text: What is the purpose of the <head> tag in an HTML document?
fields.option_a: To display content on the page
fields.option_b: To contain meta-information about the document
fields.option_c: To create links to other pages
fields.option_d: To add images to the page
fields.explanation: Explanation: The <head> tag contains meta-information about the document, such as the title, character set, and links to stylesheets.

fields.text: What does the <title> tag define in an HTML document?
fields.option_a: The main heading of the page
fields.option_b: The title of the webpage that appears in the browser tab
fields.option_c: The title of the document file
fields.explanation: The <title> tag defines the title of the webpage, which appears in the browser's title bar or tab.

fields.text: Which tag would you use to define an important text?
fields.explanation: The <strong> tag defines important text, typically displayed in bold by default.

fields.text: Which of the following tags is used for creating a list in HTML?
fields.option_a: <ol> for ordered lists and <ul> for unordered lists
fields.explanation: The <ol> tag is used for ordered lists (numbered), while the <ul> tag is used for unordered lists (bulleted). Each item in a list is defined with the <li> tag.

fields.text: Which tag is used to create a line break in HTML?
fields.explanation:
Explanation: The
tag is used to insert a line break in HTML, allowing text to continue on a new line.

fields.text: Which attribute is used to specify the destination of a link?
fields.explanation: Explanation: The href attribute in an anchor (<a>) tag specifies the URL that the link points to.

fields.text: Which of these tags is used to create a table in HTML?
fields.explanation: The <table> tag is used to create a table in HTML. Other tags like <tr>, <td>, and <th> are used within it to define rows and cells.

fields.text: Which tag is used to create a hyperlink in HTML?
fields.explanation: The <a> tag is used to create hyperlinks in HTML. The href attribute specifies the URL of the page the link goes to.

fields.text: What does the <!DOCTYPE html> declaration do?
fields.option_a: It defines the character set for the document.
fields.option_b: It starts a comment in HTML.
fields.option_c: It specifies the language of the document.
fields.option_d: It tells the web browser what version of HTML the page
fields.explanation: The <!DOCTYPE html> declaration tells the web browser that this document is an HTML5 document.

fields.text: How do you create a dropdown list in HTML?
fields.explanation: You create a dropdown list using the <select> tag along with nested <option> tags for each item.

fields.text: Which tag is used to include an image in an HTML page?
fields.explanation: The tag is used to embed images in an HTML document. It requires the src attribute to specify the image source.

fields.text: What is the purpose of the alt attribute in an image tag?
fields.option_b: To provide alternative text for screen readers and when the image cannot be displayed
fields.option_c: To define the width of the image
fields.option_d: To specify a link for the image
fields.explanation: The alt attribute provides alternative text for an image, which helps with accessibility and displays when the image cannot be loaded.

fields.text: How do you create a checkbox in HTML?
fields.explanation: You create a checkbox using an input element with type="checkbox".

fields.text: What is the correct way to link an external CSS file to an HTML document?
fields.explanation: The <link> tag with rel="stylesheet" and href attribute is the correct way to link an external CSS file in an HTML document.

fields.text:
Which selector targets all

elements on a webpage?
fields.explanation:
The selector p { } selects all

elements on the page.

fields.text: Which property is used to change the font size of text in CSS?
fields.explanation: The font-size property is specifically used to set the size of the font for text in CSS.

fields.text: How do you change the text color to red using CSS?
fields.explanation: Explanation: The color property is used to change the text color in CSS.

fields.text: Which of the following properties is NOT part of the CSS box model?
fields.explanation: The box model consists of margin, padding, border, and content. Font is not part of the box model.

fields.text: What is the main difference between margin and padding in CSS?
fields.option_a: Margin is inside the border, padding is outside.
fields.option_b: Padding is inside the border, margin is outside.
fields.option_d: Margin affects text size, padding does not.
fields.explanation: Padding is the space between the content and the border, while margin is the space outside the border.

fields.text: How do you remove bullet points from an unordered list using CSS?
fields.explanation: Both list-style-type: none; and list-style: none; will remove bullet points from an unordered list.

fields.text: How do you write a comment in CSS?
fields.explanation: Comments in CSS are written using the syntax /* comment */, which allows you to add notes without affecting the code execution.

fields.text: How can you make an image responsive using CSS?
fields.explanation: Setting width: 100%; and height: auto; makes an image responsive by scaling it proportionally to its container.

fields.text: Which property would you use to set the width of a table cell?
fields.explanation: The width property is used to set the width of table cells in CSS.

fields.text: How do you apply a hover effect on a button using CSS?
fields.explanation: The syntax for hover effects uses the pseudo-class :hover, allowing you to change styles when the user hovers over an element.

fields.text: What is the correct way to declare a variable in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: In JavaScript, you declare a variable using the keywords var, let, or const, followed by the variable name and the assignment operator =.

fields.text: Which of the following is a valid variable name in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: Variable names can include letters, numbers, underscores, and dollar signs but cannot start with a number or contain spaces or hyphens.

fields.text: Which keyword is used to declare a variable in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: Explanation: In JavaScript, you can declare variables using var, let, or const. Each has its own scope and behavior.

fields.text: What is the scope of a variable declared with let?
fields.explanation: Variables declared with let have block scope, meaning they are only accessible within the block in which they are defined.

fields.text: What does the && operator do in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: The && operator is the logical AND operator, which returns true if both operands are true.

fields.text: Which keyword is used for conditional statements in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: The keyword if is used to start a conditional statement in JavaScript.

fields.text: How do you check if two variables are equal in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: Both equality operators (==) and strict equality (===) can be used to compare values. The latter also checks for type equality.

fields.text: How do you create a for loop in JavaScript?
fields.explanation: The correct syntax for a for loop involves initialization, condition checking, and increment/decrement within parentheses.

fields.text: What will be the result of this expression: "Hello" + " World"?

fields.text: How do you access the first element of a list named my_list?
fields.explanation: In Python, list indexing starts at 0, so the first element is accessed with my_list[0].

fields.text: How can you convert a string to an integer in Python?
fields.explanation: The built-in function int() converts a string representation of an integer into an actual integer.

fields.text: How do you import a module in Python?
fields.explanation: You use the keyword import followed by the module name to import it into your script.
